LD NUCLEAR WEAPON DELIVERY OR\nOTHER TEST ACTIVITIES\n\nComment  This is the first report of a Soviet\naircraft with its underside painted\nwhite. The US has successfully used white paint to re-\nduce to safe limits the effects of thermal radiation on the\nsurfaces of aircraft associated with the delivery of high-\nyield weapons.\n\nOn 2 November heavy bombers were\nsighted on the airfield at Ramenskoye, a flight test center\nof the Ministry of Aviation Industry. On 16 November a\nhigh-performance aircraft was scheduled from this field\nto Semipalatinsk, where tests of air-dropped, large-yield\nnuclear weapons were in progress. The coincidence be-\ntween the first sighting of a white-painted aircraft and the\nfirst Soviet air drops of high-yield weapons suggests that\nthe aircraft apparently landing at Ramenskoye, southeast\nof Moscow, may have been used in weapon drops or in\nother activities connected with the recent Soviet nuclear\nweapons tests. The sighting in any case indicates that at\nleast one BISON has been specially prepared for deliver-\ning or participating in tests of high-yield nuclear weapons.\n\n(Prepared jointly by OCI and OSI", "token_count": 189, "token_end_0based": 188, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "1 soviet jet heavy bomber specially prepared for high-yield nuclear weapon delivery or other test activities comment this is the first report of a soviet aircraft with its underside painted white the us has successfully used white paint to re duce to safe limits the effects of thermal radiation on the surfaces of aircraft associated with the delivery of high yield weapons on 2 november heavy bombers were sighted on the airfield at ramenskoye a flight test center of the ministry of aviation industry on 16 november a high-performance aircraft was scheduled from this field to semipalatinsk where tests of air-dropped large-yield nuclear weapons were in progress the coincidence be tween the first sighting of a white-painted aircraft and the first soviet air drops of high-yield weapons suggests that the aircraft apparently landing at ramenskoye southeast of moscow may have been used in weapon drops or in other activities connected with the recent soviet nuclear weapons tests the sighting in any case indicates that at least one bison has been specially prepared for deliver ing or participating in tests of high-yield nuclear weapons prepared jointly by oci and osi", "unred_source_page": 4}
